Items.Name: Slumber Party Panic
Items.Overview: Finn and Princess Bubblegum must protect the Candy Kingdom from a horde of candy zombies they accidentally created.

Items.Name: Trouble in Lumpy Space
Items.Overview: Finn must travel to Lumpy Space to find a cure that will save Jake, who was accidentally bitten by Lumpy Space Princess at a tea party.

Items.Name: Prisoners of Love
Items.Overview: When the Ice King kidnaps a number of princesses he sees as potential brides, Finn and Jake team with the prisoners to set everybody free.

Items.Name: Tree Trunks
Items.Overview: Finn and Jake join Tree Trunks in search for the rare Crystal Gem Apple, but question whether Tree Trunks has what it takes to adventure.

Items.Name: The Enchiridion!
Items.Overview: Finn and Jake go on a quest for a magical book that would prove them worthy of being righteous heroes.

Items.Name: The Jiggler
Items.Overview: A jiggly creature attracted by Finn's auto-tuned singing follows Finn and Jake home but soon feels ill effects of separation from its family.

Items.Name: Ricardio the Heart Guy
Items.Overview: When a Heart Guy named Ricardio comes to Candy Kingdom, Finn gets really jealous and finds a way to get him out of the Land of Ooo.

Items.Name: Business Time
Items.Overview: When Finn and Jake discover a group of businessmen frozen in an iceberg, the duo thaws them and hires them to help with their adventures.

Items.Name: My Two Favorite People
Items.Overview: Jake's plan to spend time with both Lady Rainicorn and Finn backfires.

Items.Name: Memories of Boom Boom Mountain
Items.Overview: Finn reflects on an upsetting experience in his past and pledges to help everyone in town, but this proves more difficult than imagined.

Items.Name: Wizard
Items.Overview: Finn and Jake temporarily get magic powers from an evil wizard, but are tricked into helping stop a comet.

Items.Name: Evicted!
Items.Overview: Finn and Jake search the land of Ooo for a new home after Marceline claims the duo's treehouse as her own.

Items.Name: City of Thieves
Items.Overview: Finn and Jake go off to face a thief king who has been stealing from little girls.
